value.value: 巨口症
abnormally increased size of the mouth
口蓋棚の欠如
absence of the palatal projections from the inner part of the maxillary processes that fuse to form the secondary palate
口蓋棚の形成不全

decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the palatal projections from the inner part of the maxillary processes that fuse to form the secondary palate, typically resulting in decreased size

label.value: palatal shelf fusion with tongue or mandible

value.value: 口蓋棚と舌または下顎骨との癒合

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: palatal shelf fusion with tongue or mandible

value.value: palatal shelves do not elevate during development and instead fuse with tongue tissues or with the mandible tissues
口蓋棚挙上異常
any anomaly in the process in which the palatal shelves move from a vertical position in the orofacial cavity to a horizontal apposition above the developing tongue
口蓋棚挙上不全
the palatal shelves fail to move from a vertical position in the orofacial cavity to a horizontal apposition above the developing tongue

label.value: abnormal palatal shelf fusion at midline

value.value: 口蓋棚の正中線における癒合異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal palatal shelf fusion at midline

value.value: any anomaly in the process in which the palatal shelves grow toward the midline and adhere along the medial edge epithelia, forming the midline epithelial seam which disappears in later stages

label.value: palatal shelves fail to meet at midline

value.value: 口蓋棚の正中線での接合不全

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: palatal shelves fail to meet at midline

value.value: polarized growth towards the midline following palatal shelf elevation does not occur

label.value: persistence of medial edge epithelium during palatal shelf fusion

value.value: 口蓋棚癒合時の内側縁上皮遺残

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: persistence of medial edge epithelium during palatal shelf fusion

value.value: palatal shelves meet at the midline during development but do not adhere along the medial edge epithelia, and fail to form the midline epithelial seam
二次口蓋裂
congenital fissure of the tissues normally uniting to form the secondary palate
口蓋骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the maxillary or palatine shelves that comprise the bones of the hard palate
口蓋骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the palate bone, typically resulting in decreased size
一次口蓋裂
congenital fissure of the tissues normally uniting to form the primary palate; the primary palate will form the premaxillary portion of the maxilla (anterior one-third of the final palate)
硬口蓋欠如
absence of the anterior part of the palate that is supported by and includes the palatal extensions of the maxillary and palatine bones in the adult

label.value: decreased palatine bone horizontal plate size

value.value: 口蓋骨水平板サイズのサイズ減少

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased palatine bone horizontal plate size

value.value: reduced size of the bony plate of the palatine bone that normally fuses with maxillary shelf to form secondary (hard) palate
口蓋棚形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the palatine bone horizontal plate, typically resulting in decreased size
上顎棚サイズ減少
reduced size of the bony projection of the maxilla that normally fuses with palatine shelf to form secondary (hard) palate
上顎口蓋棚形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the maxillary shelf, typically resulting in decreased size
舌骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the hyoid bone, typically resulting in decreased size
鋤骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the vomer bone, typically resulting in decreased size
前頭鼻突起の形態異常
any structural anomaly of an unpaired facial process in the embryo formed from the tissues surrounding the forebrain vesicle that develops into the forehead and bridge of the nose/snout
外側鼻突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the lateral area of the two branches of a horseshoe-shaped mesenchymal swelling in the future nasal region of the embryo; it separates the olfactory pit from the developing eye and the ala of the nose/snout develops from it
内側鼻突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the central area of the two limbs of a horseshoe-shaped mesenchymal swelling that lie medial to the olfactory placode or pit in the future nasal region of the embryo; it joins with the ipsilateral maxillary prominence in the formation of half of the upper jaw, and the nasal tip and philtrum of the upper lip develop from it
舌形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the tongue, typically resulting in decreased size
舌欠如
absence of the mobile mass of muscular tissue and surrounding epithelial tissue occupying the cavity of the mouth and forming part of the floor
舌のサイズ増加
greater size the mobile mass of muscular tissue and surrounding epithelial tissue occupying the cavity of the mouth and forming part of the floor
舌のサイズ減少
reduced size of the mobile mass of muscular tissue and surrounding epithelial tissue occupying the cavity of the mouth and forming part of the floor
舌突出
the tongue extends out beyond the oral cavity past the lips; may be due to paralysis, oral cavity size, tongue hypoplasia or dysfunction of the hypoglossal nerve
二裂舌
tongue is fully divided by a lengthwise midline cleft
前部二裂舌
tongue is split into two halves at the anterior tip; division does not extend the full length of the tongue; this is normal in some animals such as reptiles
舌骨のサイズ増加
greater size of the U-shaped bone lying between the mandible and the larynx that supports the tongue muscles
舌骨のサイズ減少
reduced size of the U-shaped bone lying between the mandible and the larynx that supports the tongue muscles

舌骨大角の欠如

舌骨体の形態異常

茎突舌骨靱帯の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the fibrous cord that connects the tip of the styloid process of the temporal bone to the lesser horn of the hyoid bone
